BULLETIN - EAS ACTIVATION REQUESTED
Flash Flood Warning
National Weather Service Charleston SC
854 PM EDT Thu Jul 14 2022

The National Weather Service in Charleston has issued a

* Flash Flood Warning for...
  Berkeley County in southeastern South Carolina...
  Charleston County in southeastern South Carolina...
  Dorchester County in southeastern South Carolina...

* Until 1030 PM EDT.

* At 853 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated thunderstorms with
  torrential rainfall extending across much of North Charleston and
  Ladson. As much as 2 to 4 inches of rain have fallen in this area
  with an additional 1 to 3 inches possible through 1030 PM. Roads
  are are becoming or have already become impassable in a number of
  areas this evening, including portions of Rivers Avenue where many
  cars have become stuck in flood waters. As much as 2 feet of water
  is across parts of Northwoods Boulevard. With additional heavy
  rain expected, water may begin to enter homes and businesses soon,
  especially in Goose Creek, Ladson, Hanahan and portions of
  Summerville and North Charleston.

  HAZARD...Life threatening flash flooding. Thunderstorms
           producing flash flooding.

  SOURCE...Radar.

  IMPACT...Life threatening flash flooding of creeks and streams,
           urban areas, highways, streets and underpasses.

* Some locations that will experience flash flooding include...
  North Charleston, Summerville, Goose Creek, Hanahan, Ladson,
  I-26/I-526 Interchange, West Ashley, Magnolia Gardens, Charleston
  Airport, Crowfield Plantation, Lincolnville, Greggs Landing,
  Middleton Place, Oakbrook, Summerville Medical Center, Archdale,
  Cooke Crossroads, Dorchester Estates, Centerville and Stallsville.

PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...

Be especially cautious at night when it is harder to recognize the
dangers of flooding.

